article.description: — Noah Thomasson scored a career-high 27 points as Niagara romped past Marist 83-52 on Saturday.
article.headline: Thomasson, Hammond lift Niagara past Marist 83-52
article.linkText: Thomasson, Hammond lift Niagara past Marist 83-52
article.story: NIAGARA, N.Y. -- — Noah Thomasson scored a career-high 27 points as Niagara romped past Marist 83-52 on Saturday. Marcus Hammond added 21 points for the Purple Eagles. Thomasson hit 11 of 14 shots. Jordan Cintron had 13 points and nine rebounds for Niagara (14-15, 9-11 Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference), which earned its fourth straight home victory. Jao Ituka had 19 points for the Red Foxes (14-15, 9-11). Ricardo Wright added seven rebounds. The Purple Eagles evened the season series against the Red Foxes. Marist defeated Niagara 77-70 on Feb. 14. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
